<p>Turned out I use <code>git grep</code> a lot with my VIM (using <a href="https://github.com/dkprice/vim-easygrep/issues">EasyGrep</a>
plugin). At some point this plugin just stopped to show me all the available results.</p>
<p>Due to lack of explicit <code>git grep</code> usage it was pretty mysterious.</p>
<p>The reason is that <code>git grep</code> doesn&rsquo;t search in untracked files.
If you want to search in untracked files too just add <code>--untracked</code> option to the command like this:</p>
<pre tabindex="0"><code>git grep --untracked SomethingILookingFor *
</code></pre><p><a href="https://git-scm.com/docs/git-grep">Official git grep doc</a></p>